page.title: 05ECOLOGY
page.content: Apart from the managed farmland the following habitats occur.{Oak scrub. } This exists in the bottom of the Stratt valley.{Re-generate marsh.}i.e once cultivated but now reverted to marsh as in the Lamberal valley.{Wet {water meadows.}These occur in the S.E. corner of the block around Venn.{Flora Roughly the 6 eastern squares of the block contain marshland plants and the 6 western squares are drier with an arable flora and woodland edgetype.{ {Trees.}There are many clumps of sycamore around farm buildings. What little remains of English and Cornish Elm is suffering from Ditch Elm Disease. Strong westerly winds off the Atlantic mean there are few large trees on the plateau and what there are are bent and withered on the windward side.
